## Here is an example for Portage control files.
##
syntax portage
filename /\.(accept_keywords|env|keywords|mask|unmask|use)(\/.+)?$/

## Base text:
color green /^.+$/

## Use flags:
color brightred /\s+\+?[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+/
color brightblue /\s+-[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+/

## Likely version and slot numbers:
color magenta /-\d.*(\s|$)/
color magenta /:[^[:space:]]+(\s|$)/

## Accepted arches:
color white /[~-]?\b(alpha|amd64|arm|hppa|ia64|mips|ppc|ppc64|s390|sh|sparc(-fbsd)?|x86(-fbsd)?)\b/
color white /\s[*~-]?\*/

## Categories:
color cyan /^\s*.*\//

## Masking regulators:
color brightmagenta /^\s*(=|~|<|<=|=<|>|>=|=>)/

## Comments:
color yellow /#.*$/

## Trailing space is bad!
color ,green /\s+$/
